<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="649" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Shell with very wide orifice; alae broadly-triangular with summits oblique; scutum folded longitudinally, articular ridge slightly prominent, deep pit for adductor muscle; tergum beaked, with prominent articular ridge, spur very broadly rounded; inner side of scutum and tergum orange-coloured.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="649" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Shell yellowish, conical, with six plates. Orifice diamond-shaped; scutum triangular elongated with protruding growth-ridges; tergum smaller than scutum, apex beaked, carinal margin rounded, growth-ridges less distinct than on scutum. Cirrus I with unequal rami (anterior ramus: 8-segmented; posterior ramus: 12-segmented), dense long setae on surface areas. Cirrus II with equal rami, dense long setae. Cirri IV-VI with equal rami with numerous segments; segments almost without exception furnished with two pairs very long, stiff, needle-like spines along inner faces. Measurements of specimen: basal length of shell 14.32 mm, orifice length 8.00 mm, carinal height 12.39 mm, orifice width 6.49 mm, basal width 13.76 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="649" type="distribution">
